body_html:
@zycdragonball It looks like the unit tests for shape inference are failing, can you take a look please?

[ RUN ] SparseOpsTest.SparseTensorDenseMatMul_ShapeFn
tensorflow/core/ops/sparse_ops_test.cc:187: Failure
Value of: StringPiece(error_message).contains(substring)
Actual: false
Expected: true
Expected to see 'must be equal' in 'Invalid input spec (] not found in dim shape): [?'
tensorflow/core/ops/sparse_ops_test.cc:194: Failure
Expected: ""
To be equal to: ::tensorflow::shape_inference::ShapeInferenceTestutil::InferShapes( op, "?;?;?;[?,?,?,?]", "[?,d3_3]") .error_message()
Which is: "Output 0 expected rank 2 but was 4. Output shape was [?,?,?,?]"
tensorflow/core/ops/sparse_ops_test.cc:199: Failure
Expected: ""
To be equal to: ::tensorflow::shape_inference::ShapeInferenceTestutil::InferShapes( op, "?;?;?;[?,?,?,?]", "[?,d3_2]") .error_message()
Which is: "Output 0 expected rank 2 but was 4. Output shape was [?,?,?,?]"
tensorflow/core/ops/sparse_ops_test.cc:219: Failure
Expected: ""
To be equal to: ::tensorflow::shape_inference::ShapeInferenceTestutil::InferShapes( op, "?;?;[3];[3,2,4]", "[3,1,d3_2]") .error_message()
Which is: "Dimensions must be equal, but are 1 and 2 for 'test' (op: 'SparseTensorDenseMatMul') with input shapes: ?, ?, [3], [3,2,4] and with computed input tensors: input[2] = <3 1 2>."
[ FAILED ] SparseOpsTest.SparseTensorDenseMatMul_ShapeFn (0 ms)
